The accusation for the Dagestan deputy became news
The Soviet district court of Makhachkala detained for two months a deputy of the People’s Assembly of Dagestan, Rajab Abdulatipov, suspected of participation in a criminal community that formalized disability for bribes.
"Kommersant" became aware of the details of the investigation materials, which shed light on how, according to the Investigative Committee of Russia, the younger brother of the former head of the republic Ramazan Abdulatipov Rajab Abdulatipov contributed to the criminal actions of the now former head of the Main Bureau of Medical and Social Expertise Magomed Makhachev and his accomplices.
Among other things, during the operational and search activities conducted by the Ministry of Internal Affairs, it was established that Rajab Abdulatipov lobbied for the appointment of Magomed Makhachev as head of the bureau, allegedly receiving 70 million rubles for this.
Recall that earlier the investigation against Magomed Makhachev, other heads and employees of territorial bureaus of medical and social expertise under his command, a criminal case was initiated under Art. 210 (creation of a criminal community with the use of official position and participation in it), Art. 290 (receiving a bribe by an organized group), Art. 292 (service forgery) and Art. 159 (fraud in a particularly large amount) of the Russian Federation.
According to the investigation, at the end of 2013, Rajab Abdulatipov, knowing about the illegal actions of Magomed Makhachev and his accomplices involved in the theft of funds of the Pension Fund, joined their activities, joining the criminal community.
Being the head of the department of the Federal Migration Service of Russia in Dagestan and having connections in state authorities and law enforcement agencies, as well as using his kinship relations with the head of Dagestan, Rajab Abdulatipov, according to investigators, “provided for the activities of other members of the criminal community”, established contacts with officials of state bodies to support the illegal activities of Magomed Makhachev and his being on the post of head of the federal agency.
After the announcement of this information at a meeting of the Soviet district court on Friday, Rajab Abdulatipov denied the charges against him.
“Of course, everything that is presented to me as an accusation today is all new to me, I am completely not familiar with this,” he said.
The court arrested the deputy from United Russia not for ten days before the indictment, as was the case with previous high-ranking Dagestani officials, but immediately for two months, since Article 210 of the Criminal Code of the Russian Federation appears in his case.
According to the Criminal Procedure Code, the investigation has much more time to charge - up to 45 days from the moment of detention.
