News.Ru: Users: Facebook works with failures
According to the Downdetecor service, which tracks the work of popular Internet resources, in some countries users have problems related to the functioning of the Facebook social network.
They arose from midnight Sunday, September 30, Moscow time.
In the US, Brazil, the UK, Denmark, the Netherlands and Germany, users complain about the difficulties in authorization (51 percent), the fact that the social network does not work (36 percent), and the fact that images do not load (11 percent).
As reported, on Friday, representatives of the social network reported that they found a security problem in Facebook, affecting almost 50 million accounts.
Peskov answered the question about the possible support of Serbia on Kosovo
Press Secretary of the President of Russia Dmitry Peskov believes that it is premature to talk about whether Russia will provide assistance to Serbia after the escalation in Kosovo.
According to him, first there should be negotiations between the leaders of the two countries.
About it the representative of the Kremlin told reporters of the radio station “Moscow speaking” on Sunday, September 30.
On September 29, Serbian resident Aleksandar Vucic said that he intends to discuss the situation in Kosovo with Russian President Vladimir Putin at the next meeting in Moscow on October 2.
The Serbian leader also planned to ask for Moscow’s support in the current situation, adding that there was no question of military assistance in this case.
Vucic noted that he would like to preserve peace in the region and intends to do everything necessary for this.
Earlier in the day it became known that the President of Serbia ordered to bring the armed forces of the country to a state of high alert.
